4 (c) By the 2026-2027 school year, the Division of Elementary and
5 Secondary Education shall revise the kindergarten through grade twelve (K-12)
6 library media standards to include digital media standards.
7 (d) The digital media standards required under this section shall
8 include instruction on:
9 (1) Digital citizenship, including media literacy instruction,
10 internet safety instruction, and artificial intelligence usage instruction;
11 (2) Digital wellness, including without limitation information
12 on the:
13 (A) Positive effects of social media, including
14 communicating, researching, and collaborating with others and building
15 businesses and relationships;
16 (B) Negative effects of social media on mental health,
17 including without limitation addiction to social media;
18 (C) Potential of social media to manipulate behavior; and
19 (D) Permanency of sharing materials and information
20 online;
21 (3) Internet safety, including best practices to:
22 (A) Maintain personal security; and
23 (B) Identify cyberbullying, predatory behavior,
24 cybersecurity, and human trafficking on the internet;
25 (4) Social media literacy; and
26 (5) The proper use of artificial intelligence.
27 (e) The division shall:
28 (1) Identify and curate resources for parents and legal
29 guardians, educators, and students that support the implementation of
30 kindergarten through grade twelve (K-12) digital media standards required
31 under this section; and
32 (2) Ensure digital media standards required under this section
33 are age-appropriate and progressively build on prior knowledge of digital
34 media standards.
